-- Peru Stocks: Credicorp, Maple Energy, Panoro, Southern Copper
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-02-28T18:20:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-28/peru-stocks-credicorp-maple-energy-panoro-southern-copper.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:34 p.m.  Lima  time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose for the first session in five,
gaining 0.2 percent to 22,781.42. The  MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD) 
climbed 0.5 percent to 2,896.25.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, gained for a third session, adding 2.7
percent to 75 cents after copper rose to a two-week high in  New
York , said Francisco Miranda, an analyst at Lima-based
investment fund NC&F Inversiones SA.  Southern Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), Peru’s biggest copper
producer, climbed 1.8 percent to $33.30.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
company, advanced 1.6 percent to $123.50 after the country’s
Banking Association said corporate lending rose 7 percent in
January from the previous year.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, fell 2.3 percent to $1.27
after crude declined in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
